{{Infobox Artwork | image_file=El Greco (Domenikos Theotokopoulos) - Christ Driving the Money Changers from the Temple - Google Art Project.jpg | image_size=360px | title=Christ Driving the Money Changers from the Temple | artist=[[El Greco]] | year=1570 | medium=[[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | height_metric=117 | width_metric=150 | metric_unit=cm | imperial_unit=in | city=[[Minneapolis]] | museum=[[Minneapolis Institute of Art]] }} {{Expand Spanish|La expulsión de los mercaderes (El Greco, Minneapolis)|date=September 2011}} '''''Christ Driving the Money Changers from the Temple''''' is a 1571 [[Christian art]] painting by [[El Greco]], now in the [[Minneapolis Institute of Art]].<ref name=MIA>{{cite web |url = https://collections.artsmia.org/index.php?page=detail&id=278 |title = Christ Driving the Money Changers from the Temple |website = Minneapolis Institute of Art |accessdate= 13 February 2014 }}</ref> It depicts the [[Cleansing of the Temple]], an event in the [[Life of Christ in art|Life of Christ]].
There exist three other copies of the painting and also a faithful reproduction in the [[National Gallery]] in [[London]], which has recently been considered as authentic by scholars in the field of visual arts.<ref name=Goshgarian-Genette>{{cite book|last=G. M. Goshgarian|first=Gérard Genette|title=The work of art: Immanence and Transcendence, Volume 1|year=1997|publisher=[[Cornell University Press]]|isbn=0-8014-8272-0|page=165|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cmo-sLMYPiQC&pg=PA165 }}</ref> Two versions and that other on loan from Madrid are titled ''Purification of the Temple.'' The one at the National Gallery in Washington is called ''Christ Cleansing the Temple.''
