{{otheruses|Speech (disambiguation)}} {{Sound change}} '''Connected speech''', or '''connected discourse''', in [[linguistics]], is a continuous sequence of [[sound]]s forming [[utterance]]s or [[conversation]]s in [[spoken language]]. Analysis of connected speech shows sound changes affecting linguistic units traditionally described as [[phrase]]s, [[word]]s, [[lexeme]]s, [[morpheme]]s, [[syllable]]s, [[phoneme]]s or [[phone (phonetics)|phone]]s.<ref name="Crystal, 2003"/> The words that are modified by those rules will sound differently in connected speech than in [[citation form]] ([[Lemma (morphology)|canonical form]] or [[isolation form]]).
