{{Infobox University |name = Karnataka Folklore University |motto = |established = 2011 |chancellor = [[Governor of Karnataka]] |vice_chancellor= Prof.D.B.Naik<ref>{{cite web|title=Vice Chancellor|url=http://www.janapadauni.in/english/vicechancellor.php|website=www.janapadauni.in|publisher=Janapada University|accessdate=8 March 2018}}</ref> |city = [[Shiggaon]], [[Karnataka]], [[India]] |country = |coor = |students = |type = [[Public university|Public]] |campus = |affiliations = [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]] |website= {{url|http://www.janapadauni.in/english/}} }} '''Karnataka Folklore University''', also known as '''Karnataka Janapada Vishwavidyalaya''',<ref>Both names used by the university, e.g. {{cite web|title=About us > Introduction|url=http://janapadauni.in/english/introduction.php|publisher=Karnataka Folklore University|accessdate=12 July 2017}}</ref> is a [[public university]] exclusively dedicated to the study and research of folklore. It was established in 2011 at [[Haveri]] district by the [[Government of Karnataka]]. Its first vice chancellor is Ambalike Hiriyanna.<ref name=times1/>
The university is claimed to be world's first university for folklore.<ref>{{cite news|title=Worlds First University for Folklore Set Up in Karnataka|url=http://indiawires.com/11490/news/state-news/worlds-first-university-for-folklore-established-in-karnataka/|accessdate=13 July 2017|publisher=India Wires|date=18 June 2012}}</ref> It was inaugurated on 16 June 2012 by the Chief Minister of Karnataka Sri B S Yediyurappa. The university is in Gotagodi, [[Shiggaon]], Karnataka, India.<ref name=times1>{{cite news | last = | first = | author-link = | last2 = | first2 = | author2-link = | title =Shiggaon opens gateway to folk studies | newspaper =The Times of India | pages = | year = | date =17 June 2012 | url =http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-06-17/hubli/32281691_1_folk-art-new-varsity-higher-studies |accessdate=20 September 2012 }}</ref> It offers degrees M.A. in various fields as well MBA, MPhil and PhD.<ref name=times1/>
