{{UK-archaeology-stub}}

'''Symbolkeramik''' is a name given by [[archaeologist]]s to a type of [[pottery]] found at settlements from the [[Spain|Spanish]] [[Chalcolithic]] and early [[Bronze Age]] such as the site of [[Los Millares]].

It made use of highly stylized designs including the [[oculus]] motif.
Another example of these stylized designs are in Morbihan, France. They are commonly known as the Carnac megalith stones. [[Carnac Stones]]

