{{Infobox artwork | title = The Glorification of the Virgin | painting_alignment = | other_language_1 = [[Dutch language|Dutch]] | other_title_1 = De verheerlijking van Maria | image_file = Geertgen tot Sint Jans - The Glorification of the Virgin - Google Art Project.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | artist = [[Geertgen tot Sint Jans]] | catalogue = | year = {{circa}} 1490–1495 | completion_date = <!-- For a more specific date (post-1583): {{start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | material = | subject = | height_metric = <!-- (i.e. in metric units) --> | width_metric = | length_metric = | diameter_metric = | dimensions = | dimensions_ref = | metric_unit = cm <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | imperial_unit = in <!-- Note: this parameter must either use the value given or not be included --> | condition = | city = [[Rotterdam]], [[Netherlands]] | museum = [[Museum Boijmans Van Beuningen]] | accession = | coordinates = | owner = | url = }}
'''''The Glorification of the Virgin''''' ({{lang-nl|De verheerlijking van Maria}})<ref name="mbvb">[http://tour.boijmans.nl/en/3/ The Glorification of the Virgin 1490-1495], [[Museum Boijmans Van Beuningen]]. Retrieved on 28 February 2015.</ref><ref>{{nl icon}} [http://tour.boijmans.nl/nl/28415/ De verheerlijking van Maria 1490-1495], [[Museum Boijmans Van Beuningen]]. Retrieved on 28 February 2015.</ref> is a 15th-century painting attributed to [[Geertgen tot Sint Jans]]. The painting was made in circa 1490–1495 and was originally part of a [[diptych]].<ref>[[Wolfgang Kermer]]: ''Studien zum Diptychon in der sakralen Malerei: von den Anfängen bis zur Mitte des sechzehnten Jahrhunderts: mit einem Katalog''. Düsseldorf: Dr. Stehle, 1967 (Phil. Diss. Tubingen 1966), Kat.–Nr. 140 A, Abb. 180 A, 180 B.</ref>
It shows the [[Mary (mother of Jesus)|Virgin Mary]] holding [[Jesus]] and surrounded by three rings of angels.
The panel is in the collection of [[Museum Boijmans Van Beuningen]] in [[Rotterdam]], [[Netherlands]].<ref name="mbvb"/>
